deals.details:
Veteran & First Responder Partnership

Hemp & CBD Opportunities for Veterans and First Responders

Pure American Hemp Oil, (PAHO) announces their Veteran & First Responder Partnership (VFRP) that includes teachers, both active and retired.  PAHO’s VFRP offers careers in the CBD Industry to qualified entrepreneurs. Partners receive subsidized pricing on CBD retail display boxes. Additionally, qualified partners receive 25% off all PAHO hemp derived CBD products for personal use and resale. 

PAHO Founder, Ian Erickson, a Marine Corps Combat Veteran, describes the VFRP as an opportunity for partners to help themselves and their community by promoting plant-based supplements, specifically hemp derived CBD.

“It is important for Veterans and First Responders to have an opportunity to participate in the rapidly expanding Hemp / CBD market through our company, which provides products at distributor pricing to sell to the consumer market. Each partner is their own distribution channel, touching their local community and chosen sphere of influence. By focusing on supporting our partners, we are free to continue researching new products and optimizing the safety and efficiency of our -Made in the USA- supply chain."

Contact Ian Erickson to verify Veteran / First Responder status.  ian@paho.us
